text: Bottle, 4.4%. Clear golden with tiny off-white head. Aroma is malt, fruit, hop, grapes and notes of white wine. Flavour is malt, fruit, hop, grapes, little white wine, little sweet, little grapefruit and medium bitter.
On tap. Pours a dark amber with moderate head. Aromas of muddled mangos and citrus. Flavors of dry fruity esters, peach, and sharp wheaty malts.

33cl. Bottle. 
Pours hazy orange with white head. 
Aroma citrus, tropical, wheat, fruity. 
Taste fruity sweets, nice citrus bitter. 
Mouthfeel dry. 
Great brew!

hazy golden colour, large white head; aroma of grapefruit, orange zest oils, mango, some tangerine, maybe grape notes, lemongrass and wet wheat; taste is the same with definite hoppy bitterness; excellent!
Licht troebel blond bier met witte schuimkraag. Geur: licht fruitig, stro. Smaak: kort, hopbitter, licht fruitig. weinig of geen tarwe waarneembaar. Lichte body. Matige koolzuurprikkel.
Drank at VCBF 10-06-17. Fresh beer, nice, mango? Not too IPA-ish, not bad.

From tap at VCBF (wheat ale with mango); golden-orange with white head. Super fruity mango aroma. Smooth mouthfeel, low carbonation. Light bitter taste, medium fruity. Long, finish with smooth wheat-feeling in the tongue.

33 cl. bottle @ home, bought @ Plus Culemborg.
Hazy golden with a big white head. Hoppy wheat aroma. Hopbitter taste. Nice hoppy wheat ale.

33 cl. bottle. A hazy golden coloured beer with a white head. Aroma and flavour of wheat, hops, spice, citrus, fruit and straw.
Bottle at yesprs - Golden yellow coloured pour with white head. Sweet fruity and wheaty with some lemony hop notes, straw, hay, light floral hoppy and wheaty finish.
Pale yellow with light haze. Aroma and flavour have a fair amount of citrusy hop.
Draft. A hazy yellow beer with a white head. The aroma has notes of straw, lemons, and hops. The flavor is sweet with notes of hops, spices, wheat, and caramel, leading to a dry finish.
Spritzig hopfiger, weich herber Antrunk. Trocken grasig, mild bitter, s√ºffig. Okay. 10/10/10/10//10

Slightly opaque, nice copper colour, big white head and central column bubbliness.
Smell is grapefruit and lime and mango, nice a tropical. Bit of caramel and resin. Hint of white chlorine.
Taste is very watery with elegant bitterness and very crisp. Nice fizz. Astringent refreshing finish.
From tap. Pours hazy orange with a small white head. Aroma is peachy and slight grapefruity. Bitter, teaish, fruity. Hoppy and crisp fruity. Lingering citrusy and dry herbal to teaish finish.
Sampled @ Festival der Bierkulturen K√∂ln 2017. Leicht tr√ºbes goldgelbes Bier. Geruch ist floral hopfig, sehr bitter, grapefruit. Geschmack ist fruchtig hopfig, grapefruit, citrusfr√ºchte, s√ºffig.

Bottle pours hazy golden colour with white (nice & lasting) head. Aroma is very hoppy, grassy as well as fruity, yellow fruits, apple, citrus, wheat malt; nice & interesting. Taste is light to medium bitter and light sweet, citrus, with a dry, bitter finish. Carbonation is somewhat low. Rich taste for a beer of such a low ABV and ¬ísummery¬í type. Like it very much. And indeed what it aimed to be: hoppy wheat ale. Well done, again!

American style wheat ale, tap at Beerlovers¬í Bar at Uiltje¬ís tap takeover there. Lightly lacing, egg-white, moussy, more or less stable head, hazy straw blonde robe. Dank aroma - more APA-like at first glance than actual wheat ale-like - with impressions of dill, cooked basil leaves, tropical flowers, grapefruit peel, white bread, lime zest, dough. Refreshing fruitiness in the onset, hints of pear, pineapple and a touch of mango perhaps, gooseberry sourish accent matching well with the natural sourishness of the wheat, thinly bready malt sweet middle, medium carbo, aromatic hoppy finish, a tad herbal and grapefruity, softly bittering. Exemplary for the style - a style most consumers in the Netherlands are surely unfamiliar with, but which can be very refreshing and elegant if carried out correctly, as is the case here.

Tap at beerlovers bar. Pours rather unclear blonde. Small white head. Smell is creamy, soft hoparoma ( grassy as well as ¬ícreamy¬í ) taste is decently bitter, nice grainy aroma. Some wheat, but not in your face. Nice balance.
Bottle.Golden colour with medium white head.Aroma of hops and wheat also citrus and grass medium body and good fresh mouthfeels,light and good taste of hops and fresh mild finish.

Gift from the venerable markoijelena. Not a fan of the sexist undertones of the label, sadly. Murky brass colour. Aroma is citrus and pastries. Taste is butterscotch, orange, and an orange cream pop. Creamy texture.

Tap @ Handgemacht - golden color, white head. taste is super fruity: mango, grapefruit, maracuja. body is medium and easy to drink. crisp dry finish. a great beer on a hot day. I was sure it was an APA btw. great especially because of the low abv.
Bottle from drankgigant.nl. Hazy yellow colour, lots of hops. Grassy, light tartness. No wheat detectable, more like an American pale ale.
Buena wheat ale, aromaticamente buena, dos dedos de esppuma sedosa y buen sabor, suave amargor y notas herbales, resinosas y citricas.

UPDATED: APR 28, 2017 Goudgeel, troebel, witte schuimkraag. Aroma: Citroen, limoen, grapefruit, mango, prima fruitig / licht tropisch en iets wrang.Smaak: Citrusschil/Sinaasappelschil scherp, behoorlijk wiet achtig, mossig, aarde, grassig, pijnboom.¬† Fruitigheid van grapefruit en mango... Van de tarwe merk je door het hopgeweld niet veel behalve een prima vol en moutig mondgevoel. Bijna medium body, afdronk is hoppy bitter, droog en grassig. Top!

Draft @ Uiltje bar. Pours a clear golden beer with a medium sized white head on top. Aroma of grass, lemon, hint of amarillo, dried citrus. Flavor is mellow, mild on all sides, but still incredibly drinkable and great session ale. Low on abv unfortunately means low body in this beer, however, I¬íd still drink this all day over any other wheat beer.

33cl Bottle @ LaBIRRAtorium, Madrid, Spain.
Hazy golden colour with a thick white head.
Aroma is wheat, citrus, tropical fruits, yeast, slightly hoppy.
Taste is wheat, bread, sweet, citrus, fruity, slightly hoppy and spicy.
Medium to light body, average to low carbonation.

Hazy golden colour, small white head. Aroma is fruity, floral, some wooden and mild wheat notes. Flavour is nectar, wheat, some wood, resin and mild herbal notes.

33cl flesje via Jumbo, Maastricht
Alcoholpercentage van 4,4%
Uitgeschonken in Keyte glas

Uiterlijk: goudkleurig met redelijke schuimkraag drink hem ook vrij koud

Aroma en smaak: mooie neus van tropisch fruit, lychee, bloemig, smaak fruitig als grapefruit, subtiele bitter, nadronk merk je de 4,4% lichtheid

Conclusie: goed doordrinkbier

0.33 l bottle from ¬íSpeciaalbierpakket.nl¬í, best before December 2017. Clear, golden yellow with a medium large, foamy, stable, white head. Sweetish, fruity-grassy aroma of pineapple, lemon and fresh grass. Slightly sweetish, slightly bitter, very fruity-grassy taste of pineapple, lemon and fresh grass, followed by a short, rather dry-bitter, grassy finish. Almost medium-bodied, quite effervescent mouthfeel, soft carbonation. Nice!

10/III/17 - 33cl bottle from Bierhalle Deconinck (Vichte) @ home - BB: 16/XII/17 (2017-373) 
Clear blond to orange beer, big creamy off-white head, unstable, dissipates quickly, bit adhesive, leaving a nice lacing in the glass. Aroma: tropical fruits, pineapple, mango, bit sweet, some caramel. MF: lively carbon, medium to light body. Taste: fruity start, some mango, lychee, nice bitterness, very dry, grapefruit. Aftertaste: more grapefruit, bitter hops, some tropical fruits, bit resinous, piny, grapefruit, orange zest, caramel malts, nice one!

Bottle from Cotteridge Wines; slightly hazy golden yellow pour with a bubbly white head, aroma does have some pleasant tropical hop action, taste has smooth pine, mellow malts, not getting much wheat, which is a good thing for me.
On tap. Hazy golden color. More fruity than I was expecting, but it was a very good beer for the style.

(Uiltje Miss Hooter) Bottle 330 ml at home, served into a shaker, ABV 4.4%
Bright golden yellow colour on the body, huge and thick white head on top, very good retention. 
Aroma has light wheat, grass, juicy hops.
Taste of wheat, citrus, grass, pineapple. 
Thin body, good carbonation. 
Very nice.

Bottled. Thanks to Robbert. Aroma has lots of grapefruits/citrus/lime. Hazy, yellow coloured beer with a lasting, medium white head. The taste is light-moderate bitter, very citric bit sweet-grainy, hop juicy. Very flavourful for such a light and easy drinking beer. Good.
Nice hazy yellow colour with white head.Very fresh citrus aroma, orange, pomelo. Medium body with refreshing aftertaste
Tap at Oluthuone Leskinen, Oulu. Colour is cloudy light orange with small white head. Aromas and flavors: Wheat, grain, fruits, some hops and malts. Nice fruitiness but very watery.

Bottle at Gekke Geit. Clear light golden with white head. Orange, grapefruit, light dough, dust, lemon candy, a bit of green tea, soft dank weedy hops. Under medium sweet and bitter. Just medium bodied with a bit slick feel. Very nice.

Bottle from Speciaalbierpakket. Aroma is bready wheat, intense tropical fruity hops, grapefruit, grass, peach, citrus, pineapple. Flavour is moderate sweet and medium bitter. Body is medium. Royally hopped with tons of tropical fruits, grassy notes and wheat. An impressive medium body considering the abv, lovely beer.

33 cl bottle @ Olutravintola Konttori.
Pours hazy golden color with a large white head. Aroma is wheaty, spicy and yeasty, quite citric too with hops and herbal notes. Flavor is citrus and yeast, subtle spices, gooseberries, wheat and lemon. Refreshing light brew.
3335

Bouteille 33cl, BB 16/12/2017, batch# Y16B0020.

Small white head over lightly carbonated, lightly hazy golden beer. Sweet-fruity, perfumed, rosewater, citrus. Light-bitterish flavour, ultra-diluted fruitjuice Bit rootspice bitterness. Don¬ít get any sourishness from the wheat. Wheatslcik, light body, near undercarbonated. Diluted hop- and fruitjuice.

Bottle at home. Slightly hazy pale golden with white head. Hopped into oblivion. Sweet malt, tangerine, orange peel, cookie dough, fudge, marijuana, chalk, dry grassy notes. Medium sweet and bitter. Under medium body and light chalky mineral feel, soft carbonation. Fruity, bitter, bittersweet and very dry finish. Very quaffable. Very sessionable. I just said quaffable. Amazing base lineup by Uiltje. These would all make for great great great beers at concert venues.

Bottle thanks to MonsterMagnet. My first Uiltje Brewing rating. Aroma: Intensive, citrus, tropical fruit, white fruit. Appearance: Golden hazy body, nice head. Taste: Dry, hoppy, zesty, tropical. Palate: Low body, low carbonation, dry finish.
Bottle at home, 19th February 17. Pours a light straw colour. Aroma is aromatic hops, wheat. Taste is clean, crisp, bitter hops, perfume, wheat character. Nice gear

Aroma:

Medium aroma of malts, wheat, orange, tropical fruit, hops and citrus.

Appearance:

Turbid/opaque golden/amber beer with heavy yeast and with a medium white head.

Taste/Palate:

Starts medium sweet with malts, wheat, orange and tropical fruit; ends slightly bitter and dry with hops and citrus.

Overall:

This beer is rather intense, complex and balanced. Great idea to match these two hops together with a wheat ale. Great soft flavours with loads of refreshing fruit, complimented by a fitting palate. Great appearance as well, but the aroma could have been stronger though.
Helder lichtgeel bier met weinig schuim. Smaak is fris, licht bitter hoppig met iets van grapefruit en tarwe. Geslaagd wat mij betreft.

33cl bottle at home. Pale golden with a medium white soapy head. Light to medium body with moderate carbonation. Subtle bitter and sweet tones. Wheat, yeast, citrus, hops and spices. Quite refreshing.

Nice golden color, decent head. Smells grapy, tastes tropical fruit, wheat grain, slight pine bitterness.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Bottle. Golden color. Aroma has white grape, citrus, malt and fresh hop. Nice taste of white grape, citrus, pineapple, soft wheat, subtle bitter pine and mango. Delicious, could drink liters of this.

Bottle, pours a hazy yellow with a white head. Lovely hoppy aroma (tropical fruit, grass, light pine) and and very tasty. Not thin at all, excellent balance. Good stuff!
Really nice nose - grainy, wheat, tropical fruits, also some nice orange and grapefruit notes, pine. Slightly candy and caramel. Medium sweet, refreshing, and fruity. Really good brew.

bottle from dutch care package, hazy blonde colour with a white head. nose of crisp grains, green apples, citrus, soft wheat notes, white grapes, light tartness, limes and sweet pineapple, refreshig light tart aftertaste, bitter finish tasty
troebel witgeel... licht grassig fruitig, tarwe... licht zoek, subtiel bitter, zuurtje achterin... fris, hele lichte carbs...

33cl bottle at home from Nederlandse Bieren Festival Wintereditie Delft 2017. Nose is grass, citrus. Body is opalescent yellow peach, head is small, white, frothy, mostly diminishing, good lacing. Aroma is tropical fruits, honey, citrus, peach. Medium sweet, light bitter, light fruity sour. Finish is short lasting fruity medium bittersweet. Medium body, slick texture, soft carbonation. Easy, refreshing fruity summer beer, interesting, nice one.

(bottle)
Aroma:citrus fruits,resin,grass.
Appearance:gold color,hazy,small white head.
Taste:dry,flavour of citrus fruits and stalk,dry finish.
Palate:low to medium body,low carbonation.
Overall:OK-ish.

Bottle
Aroma-lemon, coriander, grass
Appearance-pale, hazy, white foam
Taste-medium bitterness, light sweetness, lightly sour, 
Palate-light body, thin feel, lively, abrupt finish
Overall-very drinkable
Bottle @ home. Hazy golden colour with a small white head. Smells lovely hoppy and fresh. Tastes fresh, hops, slightly floral and fruity. Lovely beer to start with. Thin body without being watery.

donker gouden, wazig met schuimige witte kraag, aroma mouten, citrus, stro, grapefruit, gras, lekker hoppig smaken zijn matig zoet, matig/redelijk bitter, citrus/grapefruit/den, goed fris, stro.hooi beleving. medium body, dun van textuur, normale co2, en lange hoppige afdronk die ook wat droog is.

Growler brought by jerohen, 1 hr old, 15cl sample. Slight hazy golden color, medium frothy head. Aroma has lovely citrus and grapefruit, soft grainy malt and a slight hint of candy and caramel. Soft to medium bitterness, nicely balanced. Refreshing, great balance. Great.
Bottle. Blonde, hazy. Grass, tea and a hint of citrus in the aroma. Wheaty yet dry, citric flavor. Herbal, tea. Very nice and tasty.

33cl bottle. Clear pale golden pour with a white head. Notes of bitter hops, citrus hops, light malt sugar, a bit of amarillo funk, unripe tropical fruit and passion fruit. Light body, medium carbonation, extremely drinkable.

On tap at Uiltje Taproom. Hazy golden colour, white head. Aroma of tropical fruits, passionfruit, grapefruit, wheat, hint of pine. Flavour is crisp, wheat, tropical fruits, grapefruit, pine, firm bitter finish. Light bodied. Good stuff, nowhere near Dwerguil, more like DL3B or F* the Caravan.

On draft at brewpub. Clear golden colored, huge lasting rocky white head. Beautiful hoppy nose, tropical fruit, wheat. Very pleasant hopbitter flavor, extremely refreshing, lots of fruit, wheat. Very impressive easy to drink session ale.

Sterk aroma van tropisch fruit en een licht zeep achtig aroma.
Smaak is tropisch fruit, licht zeepachtig en wat mout. Drinkt zeer makkelijk weg.

Cask @ Thornbridge Pub, Den Bosch. Almost clear a bit pale yellow color, small white head. Smell and taste lightly malts, a lot of fruity hops, tropical fruits, moderately bitter. Very nice light resinous and piney notes in the aroma as well. Nice.

From the barrel at Foots Uiltje tap takeover, Den Haag. Very hazy orange with a small bubbly off white head. Aroma of big citrus, peach and light tropical fruits. Flavour is light sweet and moderate bitter. Light bodied with barely any carbonation,
